isting constituents with problems, and connecting with those who elect them. The first book to use intensive participant-observation methods to study Canadian MPs and representation, Representation in Action is a compelling portrait of diversity in representational styles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoliticianszCanadavCase studies. 0aRepresentative government and representationzCanadavCase studies. 0aRepresentative government and representation-Canada-Case studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh1 aBastedo, Heather, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBlidook, Kelly, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311141792940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483699940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774836999423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774836999/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-141792-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles